In Arizona, campgrounds at national parks and forests are closed and most services are suspended.
Some national parks, including Grand Canyon, are closed.
But most hiking trails are open, dispersed camping is allowed and you can still engage in recreation that allows for social distancing.
Many state-park campgrounds are open "for responsible outdoor recreation," according to the Arizona State Parks and Trails website.
"Arizona State Parks and Trails recreation parks, campgrounds and trails are open.